    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Key Calculations Explained</h2>
    
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">1. Loan Payment Calculation</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">The calculator uses the standard amortization formula for a 30-year loan:</p>
    
    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
      <p class="font-mono">Monthly Payment = L × (r(1 + r)^n) ÷ ((1 + r)^n – 1)</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
        Key: L = Loan Amount | r = Monthly Interest Rate | (Annual Rate ÷ 12) | n = Total Number of Payments (360 for 30-year loan)
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">2. Vacancy Impact</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">The calculator adjusts gross income based on expected vacancy:</p>
    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6">
      <p class="font-mono">Effective Gross Income = Potential Gross Income × (1 – Vacancy Rate)</p>
    </div>

    <ImageEmbed 
